what is the best walking solution for ferrets ferrets are crafty little things and are likely to slip out of a leash or harness unless it's on fairly tight if you really want to walk your ferret just make sure it's on tight and keep them in the house for a bit while you tote them around on it eventually the ferret will try to wriggle out and if they succeed at least it happened inside the house and not outside where it's harder to catch them longer term ferrets who have been in the house and have little exposure to the outside world seem to get overwhelmed and may try to stick by you though my two ferrets shiver in excitement and perhaps nervousness when i take them outside bottom line just make sure the harness is tight enough that they can't get out and obviously that they're able to breathe okay Ferret 1957 World Series Dog training Strap-on dildo Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 Housebreaking Horse Glossary of climbing terms Aerial (dance move) World Series Rabies Poker jargon 2000 Australian Grand Prix Equine conformation Shaggy dog story Ai Yori Aoshi Internal ballistics Falconry Gag (BDSM) Leash New York Giants Textile manufacturing Car handling Badger Billiards Have I Got News For You Sluggy Freelance Glossary of American football Hydrogen sulfide Undergarment Knife Snowboard Static Shock Frogman Surfing Kitesurfing Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Diving 101 Dalmatians: The Series Modem Sinfest High-heeled shoe Ecco the Dolphin Boom Town (Doctor Who) The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Breathing gas Futurama (TV series - season 2) Drifting (motorsport) Buttocks Decompression sickness Malibu Comics Electrophysiology Working animal Wheel of Fortune Horse tack Hyperthermia Hedgehog First aid Action potential Professional wrestling holds Ozzy Osbourne Social rule Ferret armoured car Paranoia Agent American football strategy Pittsburgh Pirates The Death Gate Cycle Offensive team Sandy Koufax Fecal incontinence X-ray Brewery Paratrooper Hors